,Recommended,270850,10863556,"Posted: 27 June, 2014",all,Stephen,"I have zero real-world knowledge about cars, or how they work.I do not have any idea how accurate the parts in the game would relate to the real-world, but I figure it has to be good enough to give you a pretty decent overall idea of how cars work, and where parts would be, and how all the parts fit together.That being said, I really like this game! Each work order requires you to think about the problem, and then identify the right part, find out how to GET to that part, and then either repairing the part, or replacing it.The interface/controls feel slightly awkward, but still much better than many of the other ""____ Simulator"" games that have been coming out recently.Even if you don't really care about cars, or how they work, this game can be highly enjoyable even from a simple puzzle-solver perspective. For me, it's even given me a different perspective about how cars work.I don't expect to suddenly look at a real-life car and know how to take it apart, but maybe, just maybe, I'll at least not be so blank-face dumb about it. Not that it's a required part of playing this game, but hey, you may learn something.I definitely recommend checking this game out."
76561198361030625,Recommended,270850,30049665,Posted: 19 February,all,Johnny Concrete,"As a former mechanic myself I have got to say this game isn't far off the truth, tracking down annoying problems while trying not to go over budget on parts, one serious mis-diagnoses could wind up costing you dearly.obviously I have an unfair advantage over casual players but I would highly recommend giving it a go, it's pretty much a standard puzzle game. although the removal and locating of componants on the vehicles is highly simplified when compared with reality, it would have to be (try locating and changing an air filter on any french car made after 2010 and you'll see what I mean). also cars that feature rear wheel drive have the engine set up as a front wheel drive wich isn't unheard of but is very uncommon, but I get they probably had limits with what they could do.The game looks pretty damn good and though the test drive consist of the same course over and over again with no noticable change on the vehicle before and after repairs, I enjoyed them none the less.I think the game would be enjoyable weather or not you have prior experience with motor vehicles, and who knows you might actually learn something.Definately worth the five pound I paid for it and will definately be picking up car mechanic 2015 once I'm done messing around on this one."
