,Recommended,270850,18270591,"Posted: 30 September, 2015",all,Sunshine Speeder,"This part is for the base game.All though the game can become boring and feel like a chore I still really enjoyed it. There will be more cons then pros but I still recommend it. I know this review is a bit late seeing as how the new game is already out which looks awesome (I have yet to play it), but I finally got around to playing and beating this game. Any way here are some pros and cons I have for this game.PROS:Can “learn” skillsLots of puzzles (more of a puzzle game then simulator which isn't too bad)You get a new shop as you progress (I would of preferred to have to buy the shops)The tests you run on vehicles are pretty cool (but can become boring)May help you learn about vehicle partsCONS:Can become repetitive and feel like a choreSometimes too simpleDoesn't feel like a true simulator (more like a puzzle but still not too bad)Not many parts some don't even get used and USED parts are pointlessLots of parts are missing (compared to a real car)Strange sun glare that can become annoyingCamera sometimes does not want to cooperateNo exotic carsVery empty shop (would be cool to have coworkers working on other cars and maybe seeing customers in the lobby)End of career kind of a let down (didn't really feel like I accomplished anything)With all those cons I still really enjoyed the game. My favorite repair order was 42 which had you finding out what parts are missing, kind of wish more were like this.And now for the DLC. I have not fully completed the DLC but I did try it out to get the basic idea of it.For the 4x4 DLC I felt like it would have been better to combine it with the career mode.PROS:New Test track for 4x4 vehicles (I thought it was pretty cool)New vehiclesCONS:Things you learned from the main career (books skills) don't transfer overAll in all its basically the same so yeah nothing to special.And now for the Drag DLCI really liked this one and wish the main career was similar