76561198027719907,Recommended,270850,8851246,"Posted: 25 January, 2014",all,irmopotus,"Working in the after market automotive industry I thought it worth my while to check this simulator out.  First of all I recommend this product not because it actually captures the essence of being a auto mechanic but because I felt this was an innovative concept worthy of people's attention. This game only introduces you to the very basics of being an auto mechanicI think that this simulator is a good bases of a game, but if the developer does not add levels of complexity in future versions I would not be willing to purchase in the future.  It would be a shame if the developer simply changes the look of the garages, adds a few cars and slaps a 2015 on the title.Being a mechanic is more than just diagnosing problems, taking parts off, and than putting them back on.  Imagine you are a mechanic and you have eight vehicles needing repaired with one bay and all eight customers wanting their car done now.  In addition, you have to battle the different part stores trying to locate the parts you need to complete the jobs.  It is a constant juggling act and this simulator does not even touch this aspect of being a mechanic.Further more, parts do not come off as easily as they do in this game.  Bolts seize, snap, and get cross threaded making the repair more difficult and resulting in a lot of lost time.  The time of the mechanic is very important.  The quicker the mechanic can complete the job the faster they get paid and get the next vehicle in their garage.  Mechanics receive their pay through their labor which is determined by the amount of time it takes to reasonably complete a repair job.  If a repair job takes longer than expected the mechanic loses money and has an upset customer.  This is also not captured in the simulator.This simulator does not let you misdiagnose a problem.  mechanics screw up all the time causing themselves lost time trying to fix the problem and make things right with their customer.  This game does not let you advance until you have complete the entire repair job correctly.Future versions of this game  could have a lot of potential.  If I was rating this game from 1 - 10 I would give it a 6."
