76561198126560604,Recommended,270850,16233257,"Posted: 6 June, 2015",all,OldHippieGamer,"I bought Car Mechanic 2014 last year and thought it was going to be a great game to try since I like to work on cars in real life. My laptop and desk top PC could not handle the graphics so I couldn't play it. I kept the game in hope to get a better PC that could run the graphics. It was worth the wait! I got a gaming PC and played the game with complete enjoyment.The game did crash a couple of times at first but was fixed with the latest updates and works like a charm! I stayed up last night and finished all 76 orders in career and 4x4 and now am working on the tuning. Oh by the way, you get a very cool car when you finish all the orders in career! I took it for a test drive and it is fast! Loved the suprise! Now I have unlimited play unlocked and may never sleep again, lol!If your going to get this game, which I highly recommend, make sure your gaming device (PC or Laptop) can handle it! Check the  specs for details!You start out small in a hole in the wall garage and work your way up to a nice fancy garage with a test path and a dyno to do chip testing so you can boost up the HP (horse power) of the car! There is a way to set up the chip without just clicking the + or - countless times to get that perfect setting. I figured it out after a few tries when I noticed how they move. You'll see what I mean when you play it.Another feature I like is the test track outside the garage! The career track is straight forward marked off with cones that you try not to hit to complete each of the 4 test runs. The 4x4 has the same test track but with mounds of dirt to really test the suspension and can be very hard to controll but do-able if your careful. Then the tuning track which is a straight 1/4 mile track to test the cars for drag racing, which by the way has it's own upgrades in the garage to buy to boost HP. Love that!I have had no glitches in the game play at all since the updates and really enjoyed my time playing it! 2 thumbs up!This game is worth the money you pay for it!"
,Recommended,270850,10819045,"Posted: 25 June, 2014",all,Jackie Shay,"Car Mechanic Simulator 2014 is a very basic representation of automotive repair, you really need to have at least some interest in automobiles or an interest in being a handyman to find enjoyment in this game. You'll delve into the life of an automotive mechanic, starting out in a basic ""shade tree"" style garage and work your way into more professional garages, which is a neat.The depth of which the game delves into auto-repair in my experience with the game so far, has been very basic; but a couple steps above ""Gearhead Garage"" of yester-year. If you aren't very knowledgable in the automotive service arena, you might find this game entertaining in it's own right.However, if you are knowledgable with cars and car repair; you're going to find yourself pointing out flaws in the details of this game. For example: The lower suspension arm on the cars in game doesn't look like it would work because only one side that mounts to the chassis is designed to pivot while the other side is a solid mount. And $200 oil changes.Beyond that, the camera movement controls can be frustrating at times. In dissassemble/assemble mode the camera orbits around a selected object, which often makes some parts difficult to select or view. Once you get used to it you'll figure out quickly how to work around it.The test drive feature is pretty much useless in my experience with the game, I've test driven cars numberous times and this feature just doesn't communicate problems like you'd expect. I've never heard an odd sound, or experienced problems with the handling or performance of cars I've test driven. And if you have any knowledge of cars at all you can pretty much track down issues with just a few clicks of the mouse.If you're an autoentusiast like myself, I don't think this game will scratch that tinkering itch for very long. If you aren't an autoenthusiast, or very knowledgable of automobiles; this game could serve as a basic introduction to auto repair.But the important question is: ""Is it fun?"" Sure, I enjoyed playing it for a little while; but due to certain details and a lack of interesting cars to work on, I lost interest."
