,Recommended,270850,8966486,"Posted: 3 February, 2014",all,macias,"Let's first define this game. Most people sees this game as similar to 2 games: Street Rod and Gearhead Garage. To be honest, it doesn't have much in common with the first one, as in SR your main goal was to race, and tune your car rather than repair it. From the other hand it's also not exactly Gearhead Garage, as in that one your main goal was to buy a car, repair it and re-sell. You exactly knew what’s broken in the car you had and you just had to click through repair process.This game is actually about diagnosing, repairing cars and charging people for that. You don't have everything given at the beginning and you have to figure out what's wrong on your own. It has a good learning curve, however it’s good to have at least some basic knowledge of what car consist of. At the beginning you only have access to test drive, but later on you get more powerful test tools, but also you get harder and harder tasks with not clear description.I can definitely recommend that game to any car fan and to anyone who wants to get some basic knowledge of what can break in his car, and how to repair it. It has a good example of what happens when you don’t have required knowledge and the garage can charge you thousands $$ for things as simple as change of the air filter. With it's price, and promise from developers to add new content soon, it's definitely worth getting.The only cons are no real tutorial for people not knowing basics of car mechanics, and small variety of cars/engines.It also has some references to Street Rod and to old Polish car history, but you have to find them on your own :)"
