,Recommended,270850,9621820,"Posted: 24 March, 2014",all,Karegian,"Some people are complaining that this isn't as detailed as they'd like it to be, or that it's not a true mechanic simulator.  I don't think it's meant to be...otherwise we could use this as the first step in a Mechanics qualification.  (Which would be cool by the way!)I like to think of it as a puzzle game.  I mean, what is being a mechanic, if it's not a puzzle?  You have to find out what's wrong and fix it.  Same thing here.  Except, it doesn't overwhelm the player with all the aspects of being a mechanic.I would've liked a bit more of a tutorial, especially when you get your new garages, as when I got the 3rd garage, it asked me to do a chip tuning.  I had no idea what this meant.  Just looking around, I found a new door...went in, and then haphazardly clicked on things, until it worked.  Yeah, there's a little 'guide' in the chip tuning, but it doesn't tell you much.It might get repetitive...but, think about it.  If you're a proper mechanic, surely you've done the same things over and over...so it does give you a sense of what it's like in that respect.The only downside...is the test track.  On the repair orders, it could say ""There's a horrid noise when I change gear"", or ""When I go faster, there's this whining from the rear of my car.""Well...there isn't.  When you get one of those jobs, and go out in the car...you expect to hear what the client is talking about...but you don't.  That would've been a great thing...to hear and feel the car handling differently, based on what was wrong.  But, it seems that the test track, and even the path test indoors, are just formalities, with no real indication to you, the player, as to what's wrong.  It's just a way to automatically highlight problems when you're examining the car.It would've been so much nicer, and realistic, if these problems were actually in the test track area...The only one that is reflected in the test track...is when the problem is, that the car wont even start.  At least that one's there...lol.This is a Car Mechanic simulator, as much as Farming Simulator is a simulator for farming.  It's got the basics, and honestly, if they added more, it could be so much better.  The framework is there...I enjoy this game, and I can see myself playing for a long time.  Especially if they let the modding community at it."
