,Recommended,270850,11163394,"Posted: 10 July, 2014",all,hardeh,"Fun game. Not realistic, but fun in it's own wayYou trying to repair cars, sometimes there is orders with direct instructions like ""replace oil filter"" and sometimes there is orders with description of the problem like ""weird noises from engine"" or ""bad steering"". You need to examine car parts and replace (or repair, if possible) them.Some parts can be examined by just looking at them, some needs to be dismantled.There is some tools to help you with that - read data from on-board computer, run a test drive or use diagnostic stand to check out brakes and suspension. After that, you will see condition of relevant parts immediately.There is one bad thing about test drive - car alway acts like a perfect working car, even if order states that it makes weird noise or doesn't start at all. All that it does - it reveals condition of some parts.There is also some illogical orders, like so:It states that car don't startYou checks engine, find out that electrical wires and spark plugs are damaged, and everything else looks ok. You replace them and nothing happens - order doesn't complete.I watched that order on youtube - and somewhy, you need to replace starter as well, even if it's on 60% condition (doesn't looks so bad).Fortunately, there is only one or two of that, other orders are fine.This game doesn't have all the systems that real car have, and after playing it you will not be able to repair your own car. But it's kinda educational anyway - you will know approximate layout of the car systems. And yes, it's fun, so if you like that kind of games - it worth a try. There is even free demo version to try it out - so try it, and buy it if you like it."
