,Recommended,270850,17582643,"Posted: 17 August, 2015",all,GamingNinjaSheep,"StoryNo real deep story, only thing you know is that you are a car mechanic with your own shop. You start off in what looks like your garage and then move on to bigger places as you get more money and more customers.GameplayIt handles nicely, sometimes the controls can be a bit bulky. You get a car, the customer tells you what is broken or what he thinks is broken and then you fix it. The way you do that is by examining parts and determining which ones need replacing or servicing. You can do all kinds of tests to see how the suspension is, how the engine is, how the tyres are and so on. You can change just about any part of the car and engine.You can even drive the cars on a closed course to check brakes and stuff, but the handling is really poor, almost farm simluator poor. And even though let's say the brakes are almost non existent when you checked, it brakes fine on the driving course, same with traction and speed, it's always the same no matter how broken the car is.You can magically reach into the car after removing some parts that are in the way, so you can after removing a lot of stuff for example change the flywheel or gearbox even. You would think that it will get repetitive after a while but as you progress further into the game you are completely on your own in trying to find what the problem is, you might only know that ""when I accelerate there is a clunking sound from the eninge"" or something. You can also tune cars and try to make them go faster on a dragstrip, I have not fully understood how to do this, I don't really have the know how on how to make a car faster, but not too fast.GraphicsThe graphics are really nice, way better than I expected. The cars are well modeled, so are all the parts. One thing that bugs me is that the cars look way too nice for some customers, there was one guy who had just bought a car for like 200€ and it wouldn't start, but it still looked really new out of the factory and recently waxed, you would expect it to be old and dirty.SoundThere is a radio which you can turn on and off for music, no real masterpiece music, just some generic simulator music, still good to listen too while working on cars. The sound the tools and engines make seem pretty realistic.Prize/RatingIf you are a fan of simulators and you are interested in how cars work this is the game for you. It's almost like a puzzle solving game once you progress a bit into it aswell, so if you are into that I would also recommend it.It is correctly prized, almost a bit too cheap even."
