76561198005243632,Recommended,270850,8843528,"Posted: 25 January, 2014",all,Nestle Snipes,"I should start by saying that....after putting over 100 hours of ""gameplay"" into working on my actual car (94 chevy caprice wagon...a land yacht of a wagon with a corvette motor :D )  this car mechanic simulator will not turn you into a mr. goodwrench!!With that being said though, it can be rather enjoyable, especially if you're someone who likes solving puzzles or diagnosing things (which is definitely up my alley!)...Despite it's enjoyability, I have to give a warning to newcomers....this simulator does very much indeed expect you to know generally where to find specidic parts, and to an extent, know what it does in order to diagnose the problem. Frankly, if you're one of those kind of people who have never seen the engine bay of your car (which is perfectly ok!)...chances are you won't find this very interesting in the least bit. Ultimately...this is more or less a ""diagnostic simulator"" more than a car mechanic simulator.,,knowledge of a parts' function will prove invaluable!Another thing to note, the english translation is (though mostly understandable) a smidge sloppy......so occasionally you'll get a problem to diagnose that can be a little....misleading, if you will...nothing too bad though.The graphics, I have to say, is definitely one of it's strong points.....honestly one of the best looking simulators I've seen as of late. I must also note the soundtrack.....though it may not be everyone's cup of tea, I find it pretty enjoyable, and it's long enough to where I didn't seem to find it too repetitive, even after 5 hours straight of playing.....and if you're wondering, it's primarily DnB and Dubstep.Overall, if you're a car guy or gal, and you at least somewhat know your way around an engine and drivetrain...this might prove pretty enjoyable.If chilling out in your garage wrenching on your car for an evening is something that you'd willingly do...this might prove pretty enjoyable.If you're looking for a software that will turn you into a legitimate mechanic,,,you should probably look elsewhere.If you're someone like a very special lady of mine, who is totally loveable and extraordinarily smart in certain aspects of life but couldn't identify a starter from an alternator.....you should probably look elsewhere, lol"
