76561198048806414,Recommended,270850,12986774,"Posted: 17 November, 2014",all,Calriel,"Hey guys,I have 5 hours or so on the clock for this droll lil game called Car Mechanic Sim! I personally know next to nothing about cars, and while awaiting Dragon Age's impending release, I needed to kill a few hours and I thought I'd learn a lot from the game.What I got out of it:* I know a LOT more about car parts and their location.* I have a basic grasp of replacing car parts.* I got more enthusiastic about cars.* I had a fair amount of fun for a few hours.What I did not get out of it:* An intuitive interface (it's quite cumbersome and the camera is dreadful).* Knowing how to tell when a part is bad.* Learning what different parts do.* Really finding out  how to do it (the game has a necessary level of superficiality).All-in-all not a terrific or extremely realistic simulation, with actually pretty poor controls and very little in the sense of helpful tips or tutorials, but for the few bucks I spent on it, I do feel I learned a lot of useful things and I had fun learning them!"
76561198018106956,Recommended,270850,12937052,"Posted: 14 November, 2014",all,NoseGoblin,"If you like to work on cars and you like puzzle games this IS for you.  If you know nothing about the basics of how a car is assembled but like puzzle games this might not be for you.  For instance, if you don't already know that a fuel pump is installed in the gas tank and the filter is in-line with that pump then you will be searching for days where to find a part that is supposed to be replaced.This game will not teach you how to fix a car. However, it can give you some basic ideas into what makes a car tick as well as learning some terminoligy such as what a tie rod actually is and where you would find it on a common car.  If your a mechanic (like me) it can be a little frustrating at times when you know what needs to be replaced and it makes you go through a ton of unneeded steps to make that replacement. But again, it is a puzzle game more than how a person would really work on a car.Some things that could be added to the tutorial IMHO would be to show that you can go to the repair bench and fix some of the parts rather than buying new...I'd also like to see controller support...WSAD in the test driving portions can make you sea sick.Lastly, the graphic optimizations need some work. I play this on an 27"" iMac; I had to turn a lot of the options off to make it playable as well as reducing the resolution.  When I play it on my MacBook Pro on Windows7 I dont have to...even though my iMac has much better specs.All that said, I am very happy with this game and look forward to the new update."
