,Recommended,270850,9413456,"Posted: 10 March, 2014",all,Silent Snow,"What should I say about this game? Is it fun. Initially it is quite fun as you are presented with challenges. There were some problems I encountered with this game though. Some of the required parts to be changed are not clear. After you have solved all the campaign missions, things go downhill and the game just becomes routine and a bit boring.I just wish there were more to do in the post game experience. It is almost hinted that you can do more with the engine, but you can't really. I wish there are more parts to replace or at least a more advanced mode or set of tools. In a way it is boring since it breaks down to running the car on the diagnostic path and the test track and then replacing all the parts as you need them. Or you have to replace something on the car first to get it running and test it. However, there is no challenge to this.I did encounter a few things that I consider to be bugs. Some parts will not show their condition, unless you physically unscrew them. I sort of understand the logic to this, as you need to visually inspect some parts to know their condition, but it seems strange. Mostly I just wish there was more variety on the diagnostic techniques. Maybe more mini-games such as tyre balancing or having to set the torque on a wrench, add a cherry picker so we can do more with the engine, force the user to lift up the car to drop the transmission. Fix the radiator, fill it with coolant. Replace the sterring wheel, align the chassis.Some problems that I have with the game is that there are no time constraints. You are free to take your time without worrying. You are also only given one car at a time to work on. It seems really strange that they give you this super deluxe car shop with the impression that you are making lots of money, but I have never seen any car workshop that only worked on one car at once. Other things I have a problem with is with the in-game parts catalog. There is no way to filter items by name or by condition. There is no quick sell option. What would be really great would be a parts checklist or log. ""Inspected x - condition y, took off part x - condition. Other issues, I think there should be a keys bound to enable switching between attach/detach, inspection, show/hide body or parts condition.I still recommend this game as an interesting distraction. Would I recommend the full price? It isn't really that much, so yes."
