,Recommended,270850,18223360,"Posted: 27 September, 2015",all,Razonix,"Well, to be quite honest, I don't really know how realistic this game actually is, besides also having this limit of possibilities provided. Regardless, it's an extremely fun experience that combines not only the feeling of working as a mechanic, but also of being an entrepreneur, managing your business (and also learning a thing or two about cars). Throughout the career mode you may unlock different features and also improve your skills in order to become more efficient, or simply finding other means to increase your incoming. Although the in-game radio idea is interesting, it'd be much better if it'd be similar to the 'Euro Truck Simulator 2', where you can actually listen to real stations. Besides that, there're a few missions that can be really annoying, especially when it comes to detect some really small parts, or those that may be hidden in this place which requires you to remove a whole lot of parts just to get there. Since there's no time limit, the game is quite casual so you can have fun with it without any kind of pressure. Overall, I surely recommend it to anyone."
