,Recommended,270850,9734809,"Posted: 5 April, 2014",all,Nolander,"I'm on the border of recommend/not recommend for this game.This game is made only for a very select group - one that wants to learn all of the basic mechanical components of a vehicle, and to learn associated problems with parts.If you don't enjoy taking things apart, sometimes painstakingly, you won't enjoy this game. The jobs range from really easy to complex. Sometimes you have to take apart 5 parts just to get to one.For those that do enjoy the reconstruction aspects, it's a lot of fun. There are still a few flaws, IMO. One annoying thing is trying to figure out which side of the vehicle to approach a problem. Do I raise the car, or fix it from the hood? This can be annoying trying to figure out from which angle the game wants you to remove parts. Another annoying aspect is camera movement. There aren't enough variables to really move the point of view to where you want it. This makes things unnecessarily frustrating.Still, I recommend this game becaue it's a concept that's new, using a video game to actually learn car mechanics realistically! They could one day develop this more into becoming a full training tool for those of us unfortunate enough to not have a garage :-("
