76561198079202894,Recommended,270850,10217815,"Posted: 24 May, 2014",all,Grizzly Summoner,"THIS GAME REALLY HELPS IN REAL LIFE!!!I was a mechanic on jets in the military, so I have a fairly good grasp on tools and how combustion engines work. However, I was at a loss for the finer components in cars (suspension, belts, transmission).After reading each scenario in the career mode and troubleshooting the problems, I have found myself predicting the most common issues with a car. For example: [Engine turns off on occasion] I start with fuel filter/pump, then spark plugs/wires/module, and if all that is fine I check the alternator and belts. Ocassionaly it will be the oil but I tend to check that first everytime just like real life.If this game can give me a heads up on why these situations happen especially with more complex matters involving suspensions and transmissions, I am one step closer to fixing my car in real life!"
