76561197970655913,Recommended,270850,8885825,"Posted: 27 January, 2014",all,jztemple,"This is a interesting game. It's not a shooter, a racer, a builder, a platform jumper. Instead, you repair cars. The game genre can be considered in the puzzle catagory, although these are not mind-bendingly difficult puzzles. It definitely would help if you know something about the inner workings of a car, however this isn't really necessary as it's possible to figure things out as you go along.The game consists of a number of scenarios or missions; in this game they are called ""orders"". You receive an order to fix a problem on a car. The description given to you may not be completely comprehensive or even clear; that is part of the puzzle. Your challenge is to diagnose the problem and figure out how to fix it. The graphical interface the player uses is mouse driven and is fairly straightforward and obvious. There are some peculiarities with the camera control; the camera is focused on an object and the player has to click on another object to move the focus. It's not really very difficult and most folks will figure out quickly and intuitively how to move the camera to the best position.There are a few minor bugs but the developer Red Dot has been very supportive in providing updates quickly; about a half dozen in the first three days the game has been available. There have been several fixes, but also some user enhancements and other tweaks to improve gameplay. This is most commendable compared to some other developers that push a game out the door and then disappear. It is hoped that Red Dot continues this excellent support and responsiveness.The game, not withstanding the few bugs, is in excellent shape. Few crashes have been reported and I don't believe I have seen a single mention of issues with different Windows versions. No guarantees are intended, just my opinion based on observation. Your experience may differ. The game, for being fairly simple in presentation, is graphically very nice. The videos and screenshots don't really capture how pretty the game is. Be sure to verify that your video card is up to the specs listed on the Store page. Having a video card myself that is on the lower end of the spec range, I am pleased that even though I have had to turn down all the video settings in the game to their minimums, the game still looks very nice and there is no detriment whatsoever in the gameplay.Another plus for this game is that it is something that adults can play with children; there is nothing shocking or disruptive and since almost the entire game is presented in visual rather than textual format, it would be easy for children to enjoy.This game is NOT recommended for those seeking a deeper, complex challenge. Those folks would probably find themselves bored and frustrated. Also, this game involves some amount of simple repetition; many of the ""orders"" (missions) involve removing and reinstalling the same parts the player has removed and reinstalled in other, previous missions. Some might find this aspects offputting, but for others this will be rather theraputic; there is a certain relaxation and comfort in the familiar.Overall I would recommend this game to others, with the caveat mentioned in the above paragraph about the difficulty of the challenge. I would compare this game to Euro Truck Simulator 2 or Farming Simulator 2013; it is not difficult to play, but can be rewarding, satifying and relaxing. And the price is very reasonable as well."
