76561197970885662,Recommended,270850,13505702,"Posted: 21 December, 2014",all,Rusty_S,"The first game like this I ever played was Gear Head Garage put out by Snap-On.  The game was crude but had a huge mod group where people made real cars for the game to fix up and sell.That game prompted me to purchase this game and I have to say as a real auto/truck tech the game is very much like real life.  Every symptom I have seen from the customer was correct to the causes.How ever there is one thing that really bugs me.  The game requires removal of items to get to another item that you really dont have to do in real life.  Example is there was one job that required the replacement of the exhaust manifold.  To do this you have to remove the rear muffler, the rear exhaust pipe, the middle muffler, the middle exhaust pipe, the catalytic converter, and the forward exhaust pipe before you can remove the exhaust manifold.When I have had to do this at work I have never removed the whole exhaust system, I have always broke the exhaust loose at the manifold to header pipe connection and then removed the manifold.This is where this game in my opinion could be improved on is allowing the items to be removed without having to remove the whole system when it is not required.  Its like removal of the front strut you have to take the sway bar end link off first.  Well I dont remove them I remove the end that is attached to the strut and then remove the strut.  Like wise in the game the strut only has four bolts holding it to the spindle arm when in reality its two bolts with another three to six bolts holding it to the unibody at the top of the strut.While these complaints are minor and do not effect the game itself I still recommend the game for those that want to experience real diaganostics and troubleshooting of vehicle problems."
