,Recommended,270850,11154260,"Posted: 9 July, 2014",all,Keith,"Surprisingly fun!It's great learning where parts are and a watered-down version of how to repair or maintain a car. Of course it's not hyper-realistic; get a Haynes manual and a beater if you want that. It's fun seeing the invoice ""I hear a weird sound the faster I go and my dashboard is dim"" and knowing it's the alternator and knowing how to swap it out.The economic aspect is fun, too. Save some money by buying used parts and repairing, or repairing the existing part directly. Invest in ""management"" to get a % ROI on future invoices.The test drive feature is really nice but a bit shallow. You're really kind of forced to do it sometimes and it's really hard to divine anything from the driving experience. It'll usually just reveal the problem parts after via color so it makes me wonder.. why even do the test drive? Some more obvious feedback (loud knocking, un-steerable car, etc) would make it more valuable.The production value is nice, and it almost feels like a NEED FOR SPEED: UNDERCARRIAGE at some parts. The music is surprisingly good too.The 4x4 DLC was a nice surprise. I'm looking forward to the ""Turbo"" DLC, too. I'd love to see the process of taking a NA car to a FI car. I hope to see (and would happily pay for) more extreme modifications like engine swaps, drive train swaps, RHD to LHD swaps, maybe import to domestic swaps (bumpers / headlights / engine), to even something like buying beaters, fixing them up, and selling them on your lot, or something. LOTs of room for expansion into a genre-leading game, and a great start so far.I picked this up in a weekly deal for 7$ and really happy for this at this price. I also haven't finished the game, yet, so I might discover some of my suggestions yet."
