76561198014220349,Not Recommended,270850,10918894,"Posted: 28 June, 2014",all,otacon1,"Car Mechanic Simulator 2014 starts off in a garage as you take on the role of the Mechanic. The goal is simple: perform the tasks on the work order using your trusty wrench and diagnostic tools (including test drives), not to mention your two eyes to find and repair the various parts and make a profit.The game itself isn't terrible, the graphics are quite good and the gameplay is fluid enough, but the repetition and free-roaming aspect of the game can become tedius if not completely irritating at times. To give an example of this, take a work order that simply says ""The car pulls to the right sometimes."" You'll find yourself pulling the car apart to find the problem, then you need to walk to the computer to buy the new part, walk back, put everything back together and move on. Sometimes the simplest problem becomes a headache because you have to remove several parts to get to the part you need to replace.Walking around the car and having to work on it section by section can be a bit of a pain, but for simulation sake is pretty accurate enough to real life that it makes sense. Although, in a gaming aspect can just be viewed as a bit of a waste of time and makes some jobs a bit too long to be enjoyable. The fact that you can't create and build your own cars and sell them off is a bit of a letdown as well.All-in-all, if you want to remove bolts and replace parts all day long, this is your game. I would recommend getting it at a discounted price if you can. Although a nice little past-time game, long-term and replayability is definitely not on the books for this title. The potential is there but unfortunately it falls just short of a good simulator.Rating: D+"
