,Recommended,270850,34999102,Posted: 16 September,all,The4thDuke,"I was overwhelmed by the success of CMS 2015 and 2018, I tried and liked them a lot, my curiosity was teased by the huge discount to the series origin: Car Mechanic Simulator 2014. I have to admit, I was going to give it a negative review and not suggest it, but I changed my mind near the end, when I was about to complete the last orders. Let's find out why.PROSGRAPHIC: Despite the game is only 3 years old and doesn't offer the nicest graphic of that era, it's graphic is honest and does its job smoothly, at least on my pc, you can even notice the garage reflex on the hub cap, I've never seen anything like that! It's an enjoyable graphic with some good details for cars, surely having the entire game into a very small space helped, if you exclude the test driving. 2015 has a good graphic, while 2018 was very complained about laggy graphic, despite bringing not much new to it, especially when compared to older and bigger games.ENGINE AND CAR PARTS: That's something I haven't experience in many other games, the car parts details are pretty good, you can understand how an engine works and how its parts look like, it's still quite generic but a very good idea. Worth a mention the extra parts for the 1/4 mile DLC (included in the game along with 4x4 dlc), you can even replace parts with better performance ones, the only negative comment is the limited amount of parts, which has been ""fixed"" in 2015 and 2018POTENTIALITY: This is the best feature the game has, its potential. Unfortunately as I will say in the Cons list, it's not fully featured. What made this game successful was its potential, unmounting the entire car and working on it, both parts fixing and replacing. It was a great idea and the game deserved its success. Its potential will be mentioned again in the Cons though.PRICE: The game is quite cheap and often featured in the weekly sale discounts, I bought it at €0.59 and despite being the first of the serie and having 2 successors already, it's still a 3 years old game, not so old. Its price is also what made me change my review from negative to positive, it has some very weak points, but can still give fun for a very low priceCONSEASY AND SIMPLE: I believe this is its weakest point. There are games made for being easy and simple, to make them playable for everyone. While I can accept that, I couldn't accept that for CMS2014. It's too easy and simple, it doesn't require any skill to play it, won't teach you anything new to play it better and, if you have a little of knowledge on engines and car parts, you may notice there's ""something missing"". Yes, what's missing? Not much, the game is just that simple, I would almost compare it to a flash game. The worst part may be the lack of parts, you can't unmount arms, you won't see any piston, valve, cam gear and cam shaft for your works. Even the most unexperienced player would notice the game is too simple. But don't you worry, the good note is that was fixed in 2015 and 2018 editions, where cars can be entirely disassembled to their very last screw. That's what 2014 is missing! Too bad because it didn't express its full potential.BUG: The game worked very well until the 4x4 dlc, where I think I experienced a nerve killing bug. I fixed the broken parts like the order asked, but I couldn't proceed to the next order. That was impossible, I unmounted the entire car and built it again, no parts were broken or missing, I still couldn't mark the mission done. After hours, I restarted the order, amazingly when I was done working on the car again, it was all good. A few orders later I had the same bug, I restarted the order 2 times and no change, so I decided to unmount, fix each part or replace the unfixable ones with new parts. I spent the entire money on parts until I couldn't buy the very last part of it, a wheel. I noticed that was the only yellow part and still saying it wasn't fixed, then I remembered the yellow wheel originally had the red wheel, when I unmounted the other wheels, I accidentally mounted it to the broken side. Actually the yellow wheel is not considered broken and if I remember correctly all other parts are fine with different parts, as far as they aren't red. In the wheel's case, it wasn't. Infact I swapped tyres and the order was accomplished. That killed my nerves and made me waste several hours to find that out, I am sure that's a bug and should be fixed, to prevent players ""breaking"" the game and leaving it before the end. That's a stupid bug with an easy fix, I think that was fixed in 2015 and 2018, no reason to ignore 2014 as far as it's for sale on steam. Despite that, I didn't experience any other bug.REPETITIVE: While I consider every CMS game very repetitive, this one made it in a hateful way. Fewer parts, easy jobs, very few cars, almost each part shared by all others, always the same jobs, no way to do something different (beside 1/4 mile DLC). You can play the first 3 orders of the game and each DLC and you've played the entire game, no reason to go any further. Even the economic part of it, it's entirely useless. Unless it's not too easy for you or you're too curious to finish it, the game just gets boring. And when you complete it, gives you nothing. Once again, it's a waste of potential.LONGEVITY: One hour is enough to play the entire game, because it features nothing but car repair, the very little beside it is close to useless. You can earn money but you can only spend them for ""skills"" and parts, there's no managing of the garage, no losses, no way to invest or give it a sandbox touch. After repairing dozens of cars with the same I4 and V6, the game gives you a modified compact car with a V6 instead of I4. Nice but useless, since you can only drive it on the test track, game over. The 4x4 dlc is even worse. Beside the bug, it only features a new car with very few different parts for transmission but the same old I4 and V6, when you complete the dlc, it gives you nothing. The 1/4 Mile dlc is more interesting, you will work on performance parts to improve the cars times on the 1/4 mile, while it gives you something different and interesting, it gets repetitive again, when you complete it, gives you nothing once again. Just boring and useless. CMS 2015 finally features what 2014 was missing, a lot of cars, different engines, more performance parts, a better economic system (you need money to buy your own cars, parts, garage space and upgrades) giving the game a decent longevity and freedom, unlike 2014.DETAILS: While it features some extremely cool details like the hub cap reflex, it has some easy details missing. Just to name a few, I notice some cars have no reverse light and there's nobody behind the wheel while testing the car. They are not so important but makes them somehow noticeable among all other problems, it's the reason I would almost compare this to a flash gameFinal word: An interesting game featuring a huge potential, but left alone to focus on the praised successor CMS2015. The game is easy, simple, boring and incomplete but it can give you a few hours of fun for a very low price. If you want something more complete, I strongly recommend the 2015 edition, which fixes most of 2014 lacks"
